      pearl: "Ceftriaxone is the NP's 'workhorse' empiric antibiotic: long half-life allows once-daily dosing (convenient for outpatient parenteral antibiotic therapy -- OPAT); covers CAP (1-2 g IV daily), UTI/pyelonephritis (1 g IV daily), meningitis (2 g IV q12h), gonorrhea (500 mg IM single dose); does NOT cover MRSA, Pseudomonas, Enterococcus, or atypicals -- must add appropriate agents when these are suspected"
